label.value: retrograde axonal protein transport

value.value: The directed movement of proteins along microtubules from the cell periphery toward the cell body in nerve cell axons.

label.value: signal release from synapse

value.value: Any signal release from a synapse.

label.value: cell cortex region

value.value: The complete extent of cell cortex that underlies some some region of the plasma membrane.

label.value: regulation of skeletal muscle contraction by action potential

value.value: Any action potential process that regulates skeletal muscle contraction.

label.value: pulmonary blood vessel remodeling

value.value: The reorganization or renovation of existing pulmonary blood vessels.

label.value: vascular endothelial cell proliferation

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of blood vessel endothelial cells, resulting in the expansion of a cell population.

label.value: mitotic nuclear membrane organization

value.value: A mitotic cell cycle process which results in the assembly, arrangement, or disassembly of the nuclear inner or outer membrane during mitosis.

definition.value: This process only occurs in organisms which undergo 'closed mitosis' without nuclear breakdown.

label.value: nuclear membrane biogenesis

value.value: The process in which a nuclear membrane is synthesized, aggregates, and bonds together.

label.value: cellular response to environmental stimulus

value.value: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an environmental stimulus.

label.value: regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

label.value: negative regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

label.value: positive regulation of inflammatory response to wounding

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the inflammatory response to wounding.

label.value: neuron projection organization

value.value: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a prolongation or process extending from a neuron, e.g. an axon, or a dendrite.

value.value: The multiplication or reproduction of cardiac muscle myoblasts, resulting in the expansion of a cardiac muscle myoblast cell population. A cardiac myoblast is a precursor cell that has been committed to a cardiac muscle cell fate but retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life.
